<MELItem itemNbr="35-21-02" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-35-21-02.1.2-35-21-02_FAA">
<Title>Passenger Oxygen Controllers</Title>
<DispatchCondition dispCondOptions="A" repairInterval="B" nbrInstalled="-" nbrRequired="0" maintIndicator="(M)">
<Title>No Altitude Restrictions</Title>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated passenger seats are blocked and placarded to prevent occupancy.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated flight attendant seat is considered inoperative.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated lavatory door is locked closed and placarded INOPERATIVE - DO NOT ENTER.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated galley area curtain nearest operative oxygen controllers is secured open or removed.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
<Note>
<Para>These provisions are not intended to prohibit lavatory inspections by crew members.</Para>
</Note>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Note>
<Para>For inoperative flight attendant seat oxygen controllers, the airplane must also be dispatched using MEL item 25-25-01.</Para>
</Note>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>For inoperative cabin, lavatory and galley oxygen controllers, configure the airplane as required (AMM DDG 35-21-02).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>For inoperative cabin oxygen controllers, block and placard associated seats.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For inoperative lavatory oxygen controllers, close, lock and placard associated lavatory to prevent occupancy.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For inoperative galley oxygen controllers, secure open or remove associated galley area curtain nearest operative oxygen controllers.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
<DispatchCondition dispCondOptions="B" repairInterval="B" nbrInstalled="-" nbrRequired="0" opsIndicator="(O)">
<Title>Altitude Restrictions</Title>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Appropriate portable oxygen supplies are available.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Both air conditioning packs operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Pressurization system operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Appropriate altitude adjustments are applied.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Passengers are appropriately briefed in accordance with OM Part A Chapter 8.8.2.2 Supplemental Oxygen for Sustenance.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceNote>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>For an air conditioning pack to be operating normally, certain items associated with that system must operate normally.  See MEL item 21-51-01 for a list of those items.</Para>
